  "original_title": "\u0da7\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0db8\u0dca\u0db4\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dda \u0dc4\u0dd2\u0da7\u0db4\u0dd4 \u0d8b\u0db4\u0daf\u0dda\u0dc1\u0d9a \u0dba\u0dd4\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dbb\u0dda\u0db1 \u0d85\u0db1\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0dad\u0dba \u0daf\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Trump's former adviser sees the future of Ukraine",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Former Trump military advisor Colonel Douglas McGregor said in an interview with Sky News Australia that Ukraine could disappear from the map if the conflict with Russia is not resolved peacefully.",
        "Asked what more could be done to help Ukraine in the ongoing military conflict, McGregor stated, \"The longer this goes on, the more people will be needlessly killed. The more damage Ukraine will certainly suffer. Effectively a failure situation, it can be completely wiped off the map.\" .\" Namely.",
        "\"We need a ceasefire,\" MacGregor argued, noting that Ukraine's forces have suffered massive losses during the conflict, and that Russian forces have not suffered any significant losses or injuries at this point. He also mentioned that countries like Australia should not stand against it and force it.",
        "\"We cannot fight this until there are no more Ukrainians left,\" he stressed, adding that he had heard from people in Berlin, Paris and London that there was growing support for a ceasefire between Moscow and Kiev's rulers."
      ],
